The paper deals with signal reconstruction from compressed measurements, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of weighted mixed $\ell_2/\ell_p$ minimization suggests a focus on optimization and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the block $p$-restricted isometry property and the block $p$-null space property, which are concepts related to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and systems and control (cs.SI).
